The paper is about improving question answering models using a mixed objective and a deep residual coattention encoder. The topic of question answering falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain, which is typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also mentions using self-critical policy learning, which is a reinforcement learning technique that falls under the AI (Artificial Intelligence) domain. The proposed improvements to the dynamic coattention network (DCN) involve deep self-attention and residual networks, which are techniques commonly used in deep learning and machine learning, falling under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its model on the Stanford Question Answering Dataset, which is a benchmark dataset commonly used in information retrieval (IR) research, falling under the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category.
